Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:04.74,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,In order to conduct a force reconnaissance mission
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.74,0:00:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and uncover the secrets \Nbehind the Valvraves,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.50,0:00:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto Tokishima and the \Nothers went down to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.13,0:00:15.70,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,However, encountering Dorssian interference,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.70,0:00:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they were forced to make an emergency \Nlanding within Dorssia itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.36,0:00:26.08,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,A chance meeting with his father, the developer of the Valvraves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:30.90,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The death of Marie, who had been a Valvrave test pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.67,0:00:36.34,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The existence of the Phantoms, which harvest human Runes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.53,0:00:43.02,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,And Lieselotte, the light that L-elf had searched for,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.47,0:00:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turned out to be a Magius, \Na nonhuman entity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.45,0:00:51.69,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,She told Haruto that a secret organization composed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.69,0:00:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of both humans and Magiuses called the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.08,0:00:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Council of 101 existed in \Nthe shadows of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.39,0:01:05.20,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,As Haruto and the others pursue the secrets of the Valvraves,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.65,0:01:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they begin to realize that this \Nworld is awash in secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:15.98,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,But now, they must return home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:22.83,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,For they have learned that one of these Phantoms is on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.83,0:01:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,its way to Module 77.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.87,0:01:43.66,*Default,Akira,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.11,0:01:46.37,*Default,Akira,0000,0000,0000,,Speed, 16. Heading for the debris field.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.41,0:01:56.26,*Default,Thunder,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna take that thing down before it can reach Module 77!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.55,0:01:58.66,*Default,Akira,0000,0000,0000,,Firing angle correction complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.05,0:02:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adjusting firing timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.70,0:02:04.01,*Default,Akira,0000,0000,0000,,Fire in 5... 3... 2... 1...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:06.17,*Default,Thunder,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.74,0:02:09.71,*Default,Takahi,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.71,0:02:10.66,*Default,Renbokoji,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to recall someone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.66,0:02:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,saying that we used two units, \None would be sure to hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.93,0:02:15.53,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,That was me. This is a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.98,0:02:23.09,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,It's not working?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.77,0:02:32.01,*Default,Renbokoji,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be crazy!! You'll never catch up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.01,0:02:34.25,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep up that speed, you're looking a thermal runaway!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.44,0:02:37.01,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I have to try, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.89,0:02:57.07,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, reach!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.46,0:03:08.47,*Default,Takahi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.47,0:03:11.08,*Default,Thunder,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Haruto! That was awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.43,0:03:12.93,*Default,Renbokoji,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was a fluke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.93,0:03:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we keep fighting this \Nway, we won't win next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.66,0:03:20.30,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but right now, this is the best we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.99,0:03:26.06,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we've lost him as an asset...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.26,0:05:13.81,*Default,students,0000,0000,0000,,It's Haruto and the guys! Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.81,0:05:15.96,*Default,students,0000,0000,0000,,How have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.96,0:05:18.06,*Default,students,0000,0000,0000,,You did it! Is everybody okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.90,0:05:19.71,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.97,0:05:24.95,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto! Thank goodness you're okay, Haruto!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:32.17,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you're okay too, Shoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.17,0:05:34.30,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I have so many stories to tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you listen to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.36,0:05:39.19,*Default,Rion,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.19,0:05:40.17,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it business as usual \Nwhile we were away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.84,0:05:46.39,*Default,Rion,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thankfully. The students were hard at work, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:49.16,*Default,Rion,0000,0000,0000,,Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.22,0:05:53.74,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, them? JIORan researchers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:56.73,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,They were being held prisoner by Dorssia, so we brought them with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.73,0:05:58.12,*Default,Rion,0000,0000,0000,,Researchers?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.39,0:05:59.25,*Default,Iori's Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Iori!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.56,0:06:02.59,*Default,Iori's Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Iori! Iori!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.61,0:06:05.84,*Default,Iori,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.18,0:06:09.37,*Default,Iori,0000,0000,0000,,Is it you? Is it really you? Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.37,0:06:10.85,*Default,Iori's Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Iori.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.67,0:06:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant for this \Nto happen... I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:19.14,*Default,Iori,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you apologizing, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.14,0:06:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.93,0:06:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not making any sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.88,0:06:27.34,*Default,Thunder,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, crap... I'm getting all teary-eyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:28.69,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yamada!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.89,0:06:33.05,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,You're Raizo Yamada, aren't you? The Valvrave pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.05,0:06:35.54,*Default,Thunder,0000,0000,0000,,The name's "Thunder"! And who are you, mac?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.93,0:06:38.27,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Burnett, with Golden News.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.27,0:06:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you seen my show?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.47,0:06:41.96,*Default,Thunder,0000,0000,0000,,Never heard of it. Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.96,0:06:43.89,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,He's a famous journalist!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.53,0:06:46.24,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I asked him to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.24,0:06:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A documentary series about us is \Nairing every week all across ARUS.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.70,0:06:53.67,*Default,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,We have a lot more people rooting for us now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.67,0:06:56.56,*Default,Yohei,0000,0000,0000,,We're raising a ton of funding and supplies!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.01,0:06:59.94,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,I like to think that I'm not putting out some maudlin tearjerker.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.43,0:07:02.24,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,The increase in your supporters is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.24,0:07:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,purely the result of \Nyour own perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.53,0:07:14.11,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,Assume that we had fled without accepting Q-vier's challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.53,0:07:17.61,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,Gunfire from behind, loss of escape route.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.49,0:07:20.96,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,The conclusion I'm led to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.18,0:07:23.03,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,It won't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.77,0:07:25.15,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,Back even further?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:28.76,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,The timing of my rescue of her...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.76,0:07:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Method of escaping the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.62,0:07:33.02,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,Buying time until Haruto Tokishima's arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.26,0:07:36.42,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.72,0:07:43.21,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what I do... I can't save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.39,0:07:48.65,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,The conclusion I'm led to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:53.48,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,...is darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.43,0:07:59.16,*Default,Kriemhild,0000,0000,0000,,Resistance activity is flaring up all across Dorssia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:02.73,*Default,Kriemhild,0000,0000,0000,,The Valvraves appear to have become a trigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.73,0:08:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and fear towards our military is waning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.05,0:08:09.55,*Default,Cain,0000,0000,0000,,This gives the impression of formerly docile people suddenly acting out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.66,0:08:16.43,*Default,Cain,0000,0000,0000,,Will Princess Lieselotte's death make her a martyr for the Royalists?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:17.79,*Default,Kriemhild,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't say, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:21.34,*Default,Kriemhild,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, what do you want done with
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.34,0:08:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the captured Valvrave pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.03,0:08:25.82,*Default,Cain,0000,0000,0000,,Saki Rukino, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.34,0:08:51.84,*Default,Girl Student,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I still can't believe it. How can Marie-senpai be dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.24,0:08:53.93,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did you ever give up hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.27,0:08:56.03,*Default,Otamaya,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To be honest, tons of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.03,0:08:57.97,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was surrounded by friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.45,0:09:01.15,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your escape from Dorssiana was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.15,0:09:03.05,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you used \Na shuttle from a museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.05,0:09:05.05,*Default,Renbokoji,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It may have been preserved in working order,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.05,0:09:06.84,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but it was still a race \Nagainst the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.84,0:09:09.48,*Default,Renbokoji,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it weren't for the schedule I'd worked out down to the second, we--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.98,0:09:11.98,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The return of the Earthfall operation team
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.98,0:09:13.85,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,seems to have filled \Nthe students with both
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.85,0:09:15.49,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,fresh sadness as well as confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.41,0:09:19.61,*Default,Thunder,0000,0000,0000,,Check it out man,  we're on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.61,0:09:21.99,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting the top ratings of any news show, I hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:25.50,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Even the Beast Up Company had nice things to say about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.86,0:09:28.59,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,They say their sales have doubled thanks to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.59,0:09:30.33,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,We've also gotten offers from insurance companies to--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.33,0:09:32.50,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,This is no time to be going on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:34.15,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,You saw the Phantom, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.88,0:09:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those people have been eating \Npeople on a regular basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.13,0:09:41.51,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Just like I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.89,0:09:43.44,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.91,0:09:46.27,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,And Miss Rukino's still on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:48.96,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's the Magiuses and the Council of 101.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.10,0:09:51.33,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,We have to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.70,0:09:53.52,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.56,0:09:57.02,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Based on what Akira found when she hacked the Phantom,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.43,0:09:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,given the ship's registration number,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.40,0:10:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's probably over 100 of the things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.32,0:10:05.03,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,But other than that, we have no intel whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.95,0:10:08.57,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't even pinpoint their location,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.57,0:10:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how do you intend to fight them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.82,0:10:12.17,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Do you some kind of plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.96,0:10:14.06,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,A plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:16.75,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Face facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, all we can do is focus
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.58,0:10:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on what we {\i1}can{\i0} do and go from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.60,0:10:26.84,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Do you hate being a celebrity?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.72,0:10:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely what you kids are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.39,0:10:31.61,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,But that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.52,0:10:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fame is a fleeting thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.14,0:10:38.00,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,A year from now, people will have grown tired of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you'll be back to \Nbeing regular people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:41.95,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.46,0:10:43.95,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe that you can win?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.33,0:10:49.74,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike our viewers, Dorssia will never sympathize with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.55,0:10:54.34,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,You lack the requisite military power to liberate your homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.92,0:10:57.34,*Default,Eileen,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Burnett, maybe you could go easier on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.67,0:11:00.75,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you ever thought you're like Don Quixote here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.63,0:11:04.43,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,That maybe Dorssia is a windmill that's just too big for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.85,0:11:06.84,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,I can't
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.58,0:11:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,really say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.74,0:11:17.57,*Default,Eileen,0000,0000,0000,,That was mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:23.11,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,I've interviewed many people who successfully carried out revolutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.52,0:11:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the one thing they had in common \Nis that they were all naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.80,0:11:39.40,*Default,X-eins,0000,0000,0000,,These belonged to H-neun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.07,0:11:43.97,*Default,Q-vier,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it's a good idea to divvy up the belongings of a traitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.70,0:11:46.97,*Default,Q-vier,0000,0000,0000,,This was the color of our hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.64,0:11:49.51,*Default,A-drei,0000,0000,0000,,After all he had done...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he turn traitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.99,0:11:53.85,*Default,Q-vier,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I wanted--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.11,0:11:55.12,*Default,A-drei,0000,0000,0000,,This one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.88,0:11:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,belongs to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.16,0:11:59.56,*Default,Q-vier,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, if you want it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.77,0:12:05.93,*Default,X-eins,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did you really betray us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.80,0:12:09.90,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate all your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.90,0:12:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From what I hear, we'll be able \Nto repair Unit 3 thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:15.02,*Default,Iori's Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Just let me atone for my sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:16.25,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.93,0:12:21.26,*Default,Iori's Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'm amazed that you perfected machines like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.85,0:12:23.26,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:28.70,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,I wish that we'd had another option besides using this technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:38.04,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf? You're in there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:42.78,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,It's me. I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.01,0:12:47.52,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,I want your help with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.90,0:12:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you want revenge against \Nthe Council of 101, so--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.27,0:12:59.34,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,What {\i1}is{\i0} this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.67,0:13:05.21,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't save her, not even in simulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.45,0:13:11.76,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,Lieselotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.26,0:13:23.13,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Look, about Lieselotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.67,0:13:25.71,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.14,0:13:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing that you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.52,0:13:36.59,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.30,0:13:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:49.63,*Default,L-elf,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.77,0:13:54.49,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf might take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:56.11,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.50,0:14:00.10,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Haruto. Don't be in such a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:01.28,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,But we--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.69,0:14:03.32,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,I know things are serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.90,0:14:08.50,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,The Magiuses. The search for Rukino. The Phantoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.36,0:14:10.57,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,We have a ton of problems on our plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:14.05,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's the matter of your dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.45,0:14:18.19,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,But each one of those problems
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.19,0:14:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't something that can \Nbe solved right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.15,0:14:22.01,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:27.15,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,At a time like this, you should
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.15,0:14:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,go out on a date with \NShoko or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.36,0:14:30.59,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,It's important to take your mind off things, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.24,0:14:33.93,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about? I can't, not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.23,0:14:35.88,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we need to take our minds off things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.26,0:14:40.44,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling when we might die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.28,0:14:44.93,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,If you're prepared to die, you can do anything, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.44,0:14:48.07,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Don't regret things left undone, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.87,0:14:50.79,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.33,0:14:54.52,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.52,0:14:56.20,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking everywhere for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.20,0:14:57.33,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Shoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.56,0:14:59.12,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.64,0:15:00.71,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.97,0:15:02.21,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.61,0:15:04.71,*Default,Inuzuka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sleepy! Good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.98,0:15:06.27,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.27,0:15:07.44,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.14,0:15:10.68,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he's worn out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.23,0:15:13.71,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Shoko, you said you've been looking for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.71,0:15:15.47,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right! I have big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.76,0:15:18.98,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,The condemnation resolution against Dorssia has been adopted!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.98,0:15:21.11,*Default,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,She's been pushing for it this whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.11,0:15:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she wanted to make them \Nadopt a condemnation resolution!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.49,0:15:27.65,*Default,Iori,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, when Shoko suggested it, I thought it was a lost cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.65,0:15:30.78,*Default,Yohei,0000,0000,0000,,Before we knew it, we all got caught up in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.78,0:15:33.66,*Default,Girl Student C,0000,0000,0000,,This means that ARUS will side with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:34.83,*Default,Boy Student A,0000,0000,0000,,Not just ARUS!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.83,0:15:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say there's 84 \Nother countries, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:38.83,*Default,Boy Student B,0000,0000,0000,,With that many, not even Dorssia can ignore it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.29,0:15:42.11,*Default,Cameraman,0000,0000,0000,,ARUS has their presidential election coming up soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.11,0:15:46.04,*Default,Eileen,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this means that in the end, democracy is a popularity contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.85,0:15:49.62,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,If they ignore the condemnation resolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.62,0:15:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the next step is a resolution \Nto impose sanctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.18,0:15:54.82,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Dorssia is running out of options to avoid coming to the negotiation table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.82,0:15:55.97,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you brought in the TV crew?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.88,0:15:59.16,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I was turned down left and right at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, even Mr. Burnett \Nturned me down three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:04.50,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,We all did some digging and then started making calls like crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.50,0:16:06.73,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,And then, little by little, we found people willing to work with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:10.24,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it. You guys were all fighting up here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.68,0:16:11.90,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,It's all thanks to you, Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.33,0:16:13.40,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,To me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.40,0:16:15.26,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, in that cave, you--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.30,0:16:21.55,*Default,Haruto (young),0000,0000,0000,,It'll be okay, Shoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.43,0:16:25.62,*Default,Haruto (young),0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm with you. I'll be with you, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.77,0:16:32.05,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,And you came back, just like I knew you would!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.85,0:16:34.06,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I had faith in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.65,0:17:07.73,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Even if this succeeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.73,0:17:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it doesn't mean that anything \Nwill change right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.89,0:17:13.80,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,but we're tackling the things we {\i1}can{\i0} do one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.51,0:17:15.26,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:18.68,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,So L-elf,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.03,0:17:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll be waiting for you \Nas long as it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.53,0:17:25.77,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave some dinner for you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.44,0:17:31.70,*Default,News,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The one who chose the location for this top-level summit was--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:32.65,*Default,X-eins,0000,0000,0000,,H-neun...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.24,0:17:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe someone \Nwas able to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.37,0:17:40.84,*Default,News,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, in a certain sense, this will be seen as an historic meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.09,0:17:44.13,*Default,X-eins,0000,0000,0000,,This is a--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.70,0:18:01.16,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's pack up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.16,0:18:02.60,*Default,Cameraman,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But they're still--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.17,0:18:05.79,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Let the others get this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:07.84,*Default,Cameraman,0000,0000,0000,,Why the heck would you want to leave this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.42,0:18:09.36,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,I got a tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.05,0:18:11.14,*Default,Cameraman,0000,0000,0000,,But that's--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.14,0:18:13.05,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,If it's genuine, this means big trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.05,0:18:14.49,*Default,Cameraman,0000,0000,0000,,That's mind-blowing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.92,0:18:16.39,*Default,Burnett,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Eileen go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.35,0:18:18.83,*Default,Cameraman,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen her since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.40,0:18:25.90,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen, thank you for so graciously coming to our country today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.64,0:18:28.39,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for hosting
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this august international \Nassembly in a gymnasium.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.64,0:18:33.88,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,However, this is the current reality of JIOR.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.39,0:18:35.96,*Default,ARUS president,0000,0000,0000,,We're aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.96,0:18:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we convene the meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.62,0:18:40.03,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your kind understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.63,0:18:43.83,*Default,Magius A,0000,0000,0000,,Those children have taken this too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.16,0:18:46.99,*Default,Magius B,0000,0000,0000,,The seizure of the Phantom was an unexpected turn of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:49.03,*Default,Magius C,0000,0000,0000,,There is a high probability that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.03,0:18:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they have obtained information \Nregarding us from Lieselotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.96,0:18:54.41,*Default,Magius A,0000,0000,0000,,It is our rule to refrain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.41,0:18:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from meddling in world \Naffairs as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:19:02.41,*Default,Magius A,0000,0000,0000,,But we must remove them from the world stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.86,0:19:15.27,*Default,Miyamachi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Keep it coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.74,0:19:33.76,*Default,Otamaya,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the Undergrip, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.76,0:19:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say this will boost their \Noperational duration 2.4 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.71,0:19:39.14,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,If Prof. Kitagawa hadn't pointed it out to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.14,0:19:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would still be gathering \Ndust in the back of the hangar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.70,0:19:44.89,*Default,Otamaya,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd Prof. Kitagawa go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.89,0:19:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody else is around, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.93,0:19:49.75,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,They're not in the meeting room?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.75,0:19:53.63,*Default,Otamaya,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'd heard, but nobody was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.35,0:19:55.43,*Default,Kibukawa,0000,0000,0000,,No one was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.62,0:19:59.39,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,It is most unfortunate that delegates from
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.39,0:20:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorssia were unable to attend, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.52,0:20:01.39,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.67,0:20:08.72,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Allow me to join you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.06,0:20:10.36,*Default,Takahi,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.36,0:20:12.06,*Default,Renbokoji,0000,0000,0000,,This wasn't in the schedule...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.39,0:20:15.56,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ladies and gentlemen, I beg you to forgive this sudden interruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.42,0:20:19.94,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is a matter of which I wish to inform the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.14,0:20:25.20,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Rukino!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.86,0:20:28.21,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do you know her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.69,0:20:31.21,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Allow me to introduce Saki Rukino,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.21,0:20:34.92,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Module 77 student and Valvrave pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.97,0:20:34.92,*Default,students,0000,0000,0000,,- Miss Rukino? - How did they capture her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.44,0:20:40.37,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That she and her fellow students continue to fight against Dorssia
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.05,0:20:43.54,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}is a fact known the world over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.78,0:20:47.59,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,For quite some time, I have harbored doubts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.17,0:20:53.91,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,How could mere students hold their own against us, and then some?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.20,0:21:02.12,*Default,Haruto,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.83,0:21:07.24,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to show you! Right now! This is their secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.75,0:21:53.58,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,The wound, it's gone! What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.58,0:21:55.46,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,What just happened? What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.46,0:21:57.14,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Rukino survived?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.72,0:21:58.90,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,She should be dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.90,0:22:00.09,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,She came back to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.09,0:22:01.00,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:02.02,*Default,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,It's healed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.02,0:22:03.59,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.87,0:22:04.91,*Default,Renbokoji,0000,0000,0000,,She's alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.91,0:22:07.09,*Default,Takahi,0000,0000,0000,,But she was stabbed through the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.50,0:22:08.99,*Default,man,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure this isn't a trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.99,0:22:12.31,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,No human could do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.31,0:22:15.85,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,But she... Hey, the blood stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.19,0:22:19.61,*Default,student,0000,0000,0000,,It was really black!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.96,0:22:26.74,*Default,ARUS president,0000,0000,0000,,Prime Minister Sashinami! What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.13,0:22:31.35,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You understand what this means, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.93,0:22:37.00,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes, this creature is not a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.99,0:22:39.29,*Default,Chancellor,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is a monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.67,0:24:18.14,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, episode 21. "The Cost of Lies."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.98,0:24:20.93,*Default,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Valvrave the Liberator...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.93,0:24:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The system that will expose \Nthe truth of the world.